Vice President Kamala Harris held a roundtable in Los Angeles with faith leaders to discuss urgent challenges facing communities, such as protecting reproductive rights and addressing the epidemic of hate. The attendees emphasized the importance of preserving access to reproductive health care, self-determination for individuals and families, and working together for justice. Harris highlighted the constitutional rights affirmed in Roe v. Wade, including the right to privacy, contraception, and same-sex marriage. The participants stressed the need for women to make healthcare decisions without government interference and to work together to protect this right. Harris also raised the issue of gun violence. She thanked the faith leaders for their role in promoting healing, hope, and unity, and expressed her commitment to working with them to build coalitions across faiths.